</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1A24681F10AD36C73C11488D058865FF" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D42599215DAAD374666E81E31CA506B2" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="BA313B023B5A9EF9A72340EC2498E33F" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigillata">Feronia sigillata</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823a: 42. Type locality: &quot;Phila[delphia] [Philadelphia County], P[ennsylvani]a&quot; (neotype label). Neotype (♀), designated by Lindroth and Freitag (1969: 340), in MCZ [# 33047]. Note. &quot;Germantown [Pennsylvania]&quot; was the area originally cited by Say (1823a: 43).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D352EA94FCDD1D74A25D713AE2AE70D" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="D569D620E28F9886830F9E4530BDA11F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidua">Feronia vidua</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828: 278. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="7B68ADB61BD6DA3A7F88BE50CDB2A6E1" originalValue="«Amérique">&quot;Amerique</normalizedToken>
septentrionale&quot; (original citation). One syntype in MHNP (Lindroth 1955b: 15). Synonymy established by LeConte (1846b: 350), confirmed by Lindroth (1955b: 15).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECBFEA22126F4F75CDDF1BB1746E8D73" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="A8D20715A748D2B6BFBFBB341AC68339" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">Feronia americana</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828: 392. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="0BD2C172F9CA9B479619A45C59768E62" originalValue="«Amérique">&quot;Amerique</normalizedToken>
septentrionale&quot; (original citation). Lectotype [as type] (♂), designated by Freitag (1969: 133), in MHNP. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF9F4CE77573D0EAA88C6DC095D7570D" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="3EE294AA7EFAAA4225D6D00A37ECADAE" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbata">Feronia orbata</taxonomicName>
Newman, 1838a: 386. Type locality: &quot;northern states of America&quot; (original citation, see page 388). Lectotype [as type] (♀), designated by Freitag (1969: 133), in BMNH. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1E58DEABCB8E5BF50760241682450F3" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="5E0B8D13BFFEAFFB7E0704A372A915F2" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nimius">Evarthrus nimius</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866: 260. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="6EF1A98C128AF70A4E782322F5CB77E4" originalValue="«Ohio»">&quot;Ohio&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation), which is incorrect. Lectotype (♀), designated by Bousquet (1984a: 3), in ZMMU. Synonymy established by Bousquet (1984a: 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="527EF3692B71281EA7D64026DD568899" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="63BCE061582178D46921DDA8A3F61E2B" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviformis">Evarthrus breviformis</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 360. Type locality: &quot;Southern Pines [Moore County], North Carolina&quot; (original citation). Lectotype [as holotype] (♀), designated by Freitag (1969: 133), in USNM [# 47120]. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4FDF4B605A29DC612EA5B12F4181A560" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="34F6BC2CFE4DB432A1E8CA51F5ED0825" authorityName="Van Dyke" authorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">Evarthrus montanus</taxonomicName>
Van Dyke, 1926a: 116 [secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="AD595D657061C59EA1B3D78F70CB4CDD" baseAuthorityName="Van Dyke" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="B6B597A1485DCD7392B62DC14A81382F" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Pterostichus montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motschulsky, 1844)]. Type locality: &quot;base of the Black Mountains, North Carolina&quot; (original citation). Holotype (♂) in CAS [# 1856]. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB9542B05AC84304B713E8AEBA8E6E28" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName id="35BE4D6F0E295EBEE0C3CDB2135D2596" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1930" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolinensis">Pterostichus carolinensis</taxonomicName>
Csiki, 1930: 673. Replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="6B4B3F58627AD6AC2B6D3D8017CBD390" baseAuthorityName="Van Dyke" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="18BA7249B74A2E928B9D3FF516B8136B" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Pterostichus montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Van Dyke, 1926).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48BC4C97AF78EC474DEF7772324512F3" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="001402556B713B99C4FC41BF45C97349" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2750452F2ACC34A60C8CC2828FF8E081" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">
This species is found along the Appalachians, Piedmont Plateau, and Coastal Plain from Massachusetts to the Florida Panhandle and eastern Alabama [see Freitag 1969: Fig. 131]. The records from southeastern Louisiana (Summers 1874a: 80, as 
<taxonomicName id="810CC6A8417E1C178544419CDA34799F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis id="3E3E3E6AB2D75BCA515DFA36732B6851" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Evarthrus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Missouri (Summers 1873: 134, as 
<taxonomicName id="5B31CDFE78FB3D38B7EBD8E4F308EAB6" baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbatus">
<emphasis id="D69FF04987AC42E8BE8E051E93E1AEBD" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Evarthrus orbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<normalizedToken id="35923D2D9C653853BBAF872A54B6601A" originalValue="“Iowa”">&quot;Iowa&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Wickham 1911b: 6; King 1914: 321; Jaques and Redlinger 1946: 297, as 
<taxonomicName id="FC724C9853036B0EC64704A35D1F8537" baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbatus">
<emphasis id="E3EED963E9CDE89FA6CF7C0CFA529F21" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Evarthrus orbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and Ohio (Dury 1902: 113; Walker 1957: 270, as 
<taxonomicName id="FFC8660B206F8805FA5210C5FE9233DC" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="558" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis id="4B6C5933F8CD0D9AE49C394CA91EF227" italics="true" pageId="558" pageNumber="559">Evarthrus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are in error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
